column2: outplot <- ggplot(data = plotdata1, aes(x = josh_pc_size, y= josh_pc_time, group = 1)) + geom_line(colour = "red") + geom_point(colour = "black") + geom_point(data = plotdata1[josh_pc_h,], aes(x = josh_pc_size, y= josh_pc_time), colour = "blue") + labs(title="Graph of Time per Access as a Function of Buffer Size", x ="Buffer Size (KB)", y = "Time per Access (ns)") + xscale("log2", .format = TRUE) + geom_label_repel(aes(label = josh_pc_time2), box.padding   = 0.8, point.padding = 0.3, direction = "y", segment.color = 'grey50')
